Text.Value: But you - we see you. We know you by your true name... MAHKLOOMPAH!

EditorData.NodeContext: Kuo-Toa give overwrought, nonsensical names to their gods. Air of great ceremony as he bestows one on you

Text.Value: Go out and build me an army.
We will spread word of Mahkloompah. Your glory will sing from ten thousand throats!
PRAISE MAHKLOOMPAH!

EditorData.NodeContext: Teasing you but pretending to be super into it

Text.Value: A better name than 'Mahkloompah', for one.
A god to the fishes. A dream come true, is it?
Oh hells, why not? All hail MAHKLOOMPAH!
Perhaps you should study the teachings of my god.
If you're expecting me to drop to my knees before you, forget it.
Strangulation, perhaps. No matter - your glory will be sung, great Mahkloompah!

EditorData.NodeContext: Scholarly consideration, devotion - likes the challenge

Text.Value: So that, one day... we might destroy them.
A great deity needs a great name. Looks like you're off to a good start.
We know that you must go, great Mahkloompah. We will tend your church down here, and wait... until the time is right.

EditorData.NodeContext: Sinister - imagining some great crusade of slaughter upon the surface world.

Text.Value: You are too modest, great one. This name perfectly captures your essence - your fury.
What is to be your first commandment, oh great god?
You've slain the pretender! We knew in our hearts the god BOOOAL was false.

EditorData.NodeContext: In awe of you, rushing to affirm his faith - and absolutely means it

Text.Value: Just keep doing what you're doing.
If they ask for a sacrifice, I'd suggest virgins. Young and hot-blooded.
... you test us, great one. There are other ways of showing devotion.

EditorData.NodeContext: Slightly taken back, and faith only redoubling

Text.Value: Yes - yes! We will study this being who claims power over you, great Mahkloompah.
No more blood rituals.
Our blood to fill your oceans, great Mahkloompah! Our bones to build your temple in the deep!

EditorData.NodeContext: Fanatic - air of prayer about it, repeating exactly the same devotion he gave to the 'god' you killed

Synopsis:
The Zealot is a Kuo Toa obsessed with his new god - you. You've slain the 'pretender' he was just as dedicated to only moments before, and he's transferred all that zealotry to you.
Mahkloompah = ma-KLOOM-pa.
